        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3953447851" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16144345871527206964">I love historical fiction especially if it is accurately told. A few of Good Reads reviewers pointed me to Ellis Peter&apos;s Chronicles of Brother Cadfael series. I&apos;ve found a number of them for free on Audible, and I&apos;&apos;m working my way through them one a day. The Pilgrim of Hate is a particular favorite in the series because of the scret revealed in the last chapter. I seem to be &quot;stuck&quot; in the war between King Stephen and Empress Maude (Matilda.). What an interesting time and place to land. I&apos;ll fi</span>
  <span id="freeText16144345871527206964" style="display:none">I love historical fiction especially if it is accurately told. A few of Good Reads reviewers pointed me to Ellis Peter's Chronicles of Brother Cadfael series. I've found a number of them for free on Audible, and I''m working my way through them one a day. The Pilgrim of Hate is a particular favorite in the series because of the scret revealed in the last chapter. I seem to be "stuck" in the war between King Stephen and Empress Maude (Matilda.). What an interesting time and place to land. I'll finish the books available, and then I've got to check reviews on a book about the Civil War during this period. I wish that S. K. Penman had written one on that period.<br />I'm almost 74, and I 've always been an avid reader. I certainly wish Good Reads had been available many years ago, but I'm grateful for the service it provides today.</span>
