<span id="freeTextContainer8950008786483454389">It was an odd choice to read the 10th in the series after having only read the 1st in the series. A couple of times it mattered. Or at least it felt like it did. It wasn’t an easy book to get into. I put it down and “got distracted” by several others before deciding to finish. Actually, I started back from the beginning of the book to better reacquaint myself with characters and setting. These are very well constructed stories with very likable characters. I probably won’t seek out another right</span>
  <span id="freeText8950008786483454389" style="display:none">It was an odd choice to read the 10th in the series after having only read the 1st in the series. A couple of times it mattered. Or at least it felt like it did. It wasn’t an easy book to get into. I put it down and “got distracted” by several others before deciding to finish. Actually, I started back from the beginning of the book to better reacquaint myself with characters and setting. These are very well constructed stories with very likable characters. I probably won’t seek out another right away, but once book sales start up again, I’ll keep an eye out for one of the other titles in the series... </span>
